notesStmt.note: Folio 150v contains a geneology of the previous owner and a rhyme.
Avraham ben Shelomoh ben Shemu᾿el ben Eliyahu ben Aharon ben Yitsḥaḳ ben Eliyahu Firuz: inscribed in a note, folio 1r .
An entry recording the name and genealogy of the same owner is also found on folio 150v.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Job, chapters 23-42.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 14; written lines: 14; Uniform layout. The numbers of the chapters have been added by a later hand. Separate title page (folio 1r).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental square and semi-cursive script of the 15th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Yefet. Comm. on Job. Vol. II. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2511.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [151v].
